body:
Hello,

Thanks for the prompt reply. One of the queries that is currently slow is:

```graphql
query {
  users(where: {role: {_eq: "admin"}}) {
    id
    name
    permissions {
      action
      role
    }
  }
}
```

This query used to return results in under 100ms, but it's now taking several seconds. I have also attached some logs for your reference. Please let me know what optimizations can be made.

Thanks,
User

Hello,

Thanks for your response. One example of a slow query is when we try to fetch user data with the following query:

```graphql
query {
  users(where: {isActive: {_eq: true}}) {
    id
    name
  }
}
```

This query with permissions applied is taking several seconds. When I remove the permissions, it runs almost instantly. Hope this helps!

Best,
User
